Job Description

Acumen, LLC has multiple positions available for Data and Policy Analyst IIIs in Burlingame, CA and various unanticipated locations throughout the USA. Provide analytical support for healthcare payment policy monitoring projects for federal government agencies, including Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS). Conduct econometric and statistical analyses of healthcare claims and healthcare provider data using statistical software R, SAS, and STATA. Analyze data, research and interpret policy, and communicate findings to clients through conference calls and summary reports. Utilize statistical software packages such as SAS to conduct econometric analyses and summary statistics, and use Excel and other software to create interactive visuals for research projects. Interpret study specifications, research findings, and statistical analyses for relevant audiences. Develop research files from large confidential datasets, such as healthcare claims, provider enrollment data, and physician transparency data systems. Create and maintain thorough, methodical documentation of data management and analysis processes. Construct creative client deliverables containing dynamic dashboards and visuals to summarize extensive data and study findings for client use. Interact with project officers and other government agency representatives to access data and program information, determine analytical strategy, and present findings.

REQUIREMENTS: Master’s degree or foreign equivalent Statistics, Economics, Public Policy, Comparative Social Policy, Politics, Mathematics, Public Health, or a related field and 1 year of experience in job offered or related occupation. In the alternative, the employer will accept a Bachelor’s degree or foreign equivalent in Statistics, Economics, Public Policy, Comparative Social Policy, Politics, Mathematics, Public Health, or related field and 5 years of progressive, post-baccalaureate experience in job offered or related occupation.

1 year of experience with each of the following skills is required:
Performing statistical and econometric analysis using SAS, R, and STATA, including outlier detection, time series, and predictive modeling;
Analyzing large confidential datasets to answer policy questions and maintaining thorough, methodical documentation of own work;
Translating research requests into tangible analytical methodologies and creating quantitative models that meet research needs under time, budget, and resource constraints;
Using advanced programming techniques including dynamic hashing and constructing partitions within large datasets to improve the efficiency of data management and analysis;
Utilizing JavaScript (D3.js) to manage data visualization and data processing tasks;
Developing VBA for Excel plot automation and the creation of interactive visuals;
Performing database management using SQL; and
Medicare Fee-for-Service claims data, Alternative Payment Model alignment (provider and beneficiary level) files, provider databases (PECOS, NPPES) and beneficiary enrollment data.
All experience may be acquired concurrently.

